text.tspan: How to Put a Gradient on a Path
1- Create a narrow rectangle with the desired gradient
2- Create a clone out of it and
transform that clone into a marker
3- Create a path, adding a large quantity of nodes (Effects, Add Nodes...)
4- In the Fill and Stroke dialog box, select the Stroke style tab,
For the three Markers box (Start, Mid, and End), select the
newly created marker (identified through its XML number)
5- Edit the original rectangle to modify the grandient on the path
6- Remove the stroke of the path if desired
